main event: On May 19, 1953, radar operators at Lackland Air Force Base in Texas detected five unidentified aerial targets over a period of approximately 25 minutes at an altitude of 25,000 feet.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a total of 1 hour and 5 minutes,The objects maintained an intermittent radar contact, indicating unusual behavior,The report concluded that the targets were unidentified and not of known aircraft,No physical evidence or photographs were available to support the sighting,Investigations revealed no other aircraft in the area during that time.
witness description: Observers were radar operators and trained Air Force personnel.
